The paper deals with the RNA folding problem, which is a central problem in bioinformatics. The problem involves finding a maximum cardinality set of crossing-free pairs of nucleotides in an RNA sequence. This problem has received much attention in computer science, and the current best algorithm for the problem still takes $\mathcal{O}\left(\frac{n^3}{\log^2 (n)}\right)$ time. The paper presents a conditional lower bound for the RNA folding problem, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational biology (cs.CG, q-bio.BM, q-bio.SC).
